personalInfo.education: University of Illinois (2007, Applied Life Studies)

tourBios.carHigh: Missed the cut at the 2006 U.S. Open in his only PGA TOUR start. Has made three cuts in five career starts on the Nationwide Tour, with his best effort a T45 at the 2009 South Georgia Classic...Has also played on the NGA Hooters Tour, winning the 2010 Hawkinsville Championship.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Four-time All-Big Ten selection at the University of Illinois. Also earned All-America status...Attended Serra High School in San Mateo, CA, where he won all-conference and all-state honors. Also won the California Junior Amateur Championship.
tourBios.personal: Cites playing in the 2006 U.S. Open and winning the California State Amateur Championship at Pebble Beach as his biggest thrills in golf...Getting married was his biggest thrill outside of golf...Lists Cypress Point as his favorite golf course played. Would most like to play Augusta National...Never travels without a good book...Favorite professional team is the San Francisco Giants...Favorite TV show is "Family Guy."...Favorite athlete to watch is Tom Brady...Favorite vacation spot is anywhere tropical...Golf instructors used include former PGA TOUR player Howard Twitty.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour was T45th in 2009 at the South Georgia Classic Pres'd by First State Bank and Trust Company.
